  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT285-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">paruvam kaṇṭu vēṟupaṭṭaviṭattu vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikku vaṉpoṟai
          etiraḻintu talaimakaḷ colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER, desolate in the face of encouragement, to
          the confidante who encourages [her] as [she] has changed at the sight of the season. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT285">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vaikal vaikal vaikavum vārā</l>
          <l> rellā vellai yellaiyun tōṉṟār</l>
          <l> yāṇṭuḷar kollō tōḻi yīṇṭivar</l>
          <l> colliya paruvamō vituvē pallūḻ</l>
          <l> puṉpuṟap peṭaiyoṭu payiri yiṉpuṟa</l>
          <l> vimaikka ṇētā kiṉṟō ñemaittalai</l>
          <l> yūṉacaii yoruparun tirukkum</l>
          <l> vāṉuyar piṟaṅkaṉ malaiyiṟan tōrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Day by day being kept back he does not come</l>
          <l>and <note place="foot"> The double  <term xml:lang="ta">-um (vaikavum, ellaiyum </term>), though asyndetic, can only be understood as a coordination of the two lines.  </note> at the edge of all daylights he does not appear –</l>
          <l>where is he, friend,</l>
          <l>who traversed the mountains glittering up into the sky,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">where a single kite yearning for flesh is perched</l>
          <l rend="indent4">on the top of a Ñemai tree?</l>
          <l rend="indent7">What became, in [that] moment,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the lovely dove calling for [its] low-backed <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> puṉpuṟa peṭai </term>: or, according to T.V.G., its "red-backed female" (thus also KT 274.1 where the trunk of the Ukāy tree is compared to a dove's back).   </note> female,</l>
          <l rend="indent9">many times?</l>
          <l>This is, isn't it,<note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> paruvamō </term>: here once again the - <term xml:lang="ta">ō </term> as a demarcation of topic ("as for the season he had spoken of, it [is] this").     </note> the season he had spoken of here?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
